stack:(LIFO)-last in first out
A stack is a linear data structure that follows the LIFO (Last In, First Out) principle. This means
the element added last is the first one to be removed.
operations
push-> (append) Adds an element to the top of the stack
pop-> remove top element from stack
Peek (or Top) -> Returns the top element without removing it.
isEmpty -> Checks whether the stack is empty.

queue:(FIFO)-first in first out
operations
enqueue - element Add from rare(end)
dequeue - element delete from front side
Front (Peek) -> Returns the front element without removing it
isEmpty -> Checks whether the queue is empty.

